5:
Champion Light, we have long
awaited your return.
7:
Shakari has told me of your
circumstances... I shall place my
trust in you.
12:
Did you hear that, Light? She
believes in you!
21:
Do not forget that there is no
promise of Light ever returning to his
original form.
25:
There may not be promise... but
there is hope. More hope than is to
be found in reckless battle.
28:
Yes... I suppose that when it comes
to a choice between leaping off a
cliff and running blindly in the dark,
the wise would choose the latter.
40:
This isn't the usual power dynamic
between a princess and her
vassalâ€”that's for sure.
43:
The discussion strays. Tell me, what
was the object that you needed to
restore the champion?
47:
A World Flipper. They are doors
leading into different worlds.
50:
If we find one of those, we can get
back to Starview. That's our home
base, where all our friends are.
56:
Maybe not all of them... But I know
there'll be people willing to help.
60:
Below the Castle Excelion, there is a
hidden room known only to the royal
family.
63:
My grandmother called it the
Oracle's Hall, for there, they could
foretell the birth of a new champion.
67: Then was my birth also prophesied?
70:
Your birth was the only birth for
which the Hall gave no sign.
73:
...That explains why the court
doubted my origins. I recall being
tasked with a strange and
outlandish trial...
76:
Yes, because our cleric forgot much
of the true trial, and filled in the gaps
with his imagination... It irks me even
now to think of it.
81:
So they've also got an Oracle's Hall
here... Just like back home.
86:
I am certain the World Flipper will be
there.
90:
Then I guess our next stop's Castle
Excelion.
94: I'm sorry, but I cannot allow that.
97:
Excelion has already fallen to hostile
forces... And it is too close to this
fortress.
99:
If we launch an assault on the
castle, it may draw the enemy's eye
here.
102:
Oh... And that would be putting all
the villagers in danger...
108:
Will you not accompany me on a
clandestine trip?
113: I hope I have not kept you waiting.
120:
Where? You said you would fill us in
on the details "later," but here we
are, the day of, STILL not filled in.
123:
We will travel to the home of the
elves... the Silver Woods.
130:
Yes. You may think of them as no
more than a picture from a book, or
a fancy from a children's story... So
did most of our people. But now,
they live on our land.
132:
The world of the elves was the
second to mingle with our
ownâ€”after only Pandemonium.
135:
I hope to form an alliance with the
fair folk.
139:
But why must you travel in person to
meet them?
142:
They possess a strange magic,
which they use to close their woods
to outsiders. Even my messengers
cannot pass through. And so I must
treat with them myself.
144:
...Perhaps they will one day use that
same magic to defend my people.
148:
Will you ask them to help the
refugees?
151:
Yes. Though I also hope they will
lend some of their number to swell
our ranks.
156:
Hey, can I ask, uh... what's with all the
secrecy?
160:
You're royalty, right? With blood
bluer than a mandrill's ass. Where's
your security detail?
164:
There are rats even among the
Resistance.
172:
I wanted to bring only a select few
with me. Shakari has told me of your
skill.
175:
Alk and Nimbus impressed me. And
the rest I could see were no
strangers to battle.
178:
Our negotiations with the elves are
vital. If they fall through, we may
never retake Excelion.
180:
I entreat of you... Please lend me
your strength!
189: I'm guessin' "no" is not an answer.
193:
You guessed right. We can't just
watch innocent people suffer.
201:
Then let us strike out for the Silver
Woods. We are going to see the
elves!
